# Talks — agentic SDLC

Before non-trivial work in this repo, read and follow:

1. [`docs/agents/sdlc.md`](docs/agents/sdlc.md) — grill → to-spec → to-tickets → implement → **local preview (agent runs dev env)** → ship
2. [`docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`](docs/agents/issue-tracker.md) — GitHub Issues via `gh`
3. [`docs/agents/triage-labels.md`](docs/agents/triage-labels.md)
4. [`docs/agents/domain.md`](docs/agents/domain.md)

Before opening a PR: start the local preview server yourself, give the human the URL, wait for approval.

Root `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` add local commands only; they do not override the playbook.

Skills: `~/.cursor/skills/` / `~/.claude/skills/` (`batch-grill-me`, `to-spec`, `to-tickets`, `implement`, `tdd`, `code-review`, `handoff`, `diagnosing-bugs`). Do not copy skill bodies into this repo.
